    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-26T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="673"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5112 France/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-26T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1927—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received June 26—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>265. Briand’s Chief of Cabinet informs me that Briand wishes very much to make a
                    statement on July 4 about proposed pact. He believes it a good psychological
                    occasion. Briand would greatly appreciate it if you would convey to him an
                    expression of your views upon the draft which he submitted as he will make no
                    statement not in entire accord with you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
